The cause of the multi-vehicle accident on the N3 in Gauteng on Monday is still being investigated. The crash, which claimed nine lives and left scores injured, occurred on the N3 southbound outside Vosloorus. READ:Â 9 dead in Gauteng horror crash William Ntladi, media liaison for disaster management in Ekurhuleni, said 12 vehicles - six trucks, two minibuses, three light motor vehicles and a pickup truck - were involved in the crash. "The preliminary investigation revealed that the cause of the crash was due to dense smoke from a grass fire nearby blown across the road, obscuring vision of the motorists," he said. "The investigation on the actual crash is still undetermined and continuing."